<subSubSection pageId="545" pageNumber="546" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="545" pageNumber="546">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="545" pageNumber="546">The range of this Holarctic species extends from eastern Siberia (Ball 1966a: 131) eastwards to east-central Yukon Territory (Dempster Highway Mi 35, CNC), south to the Alaska Peninsula [see Ball 1963: Fig. 3].</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
